<span id="freeTextContainer15061745165276005568">A look at the life of Michael Jordan through his own eyes. Not very in depth, and it doesn&apos;t cover much more than his thoughts about basketball, but it&apos;s a photo-heavy 100+ page book. Can&apos;t fit much more in a book that small. <br/><br/>Good for those who know very little or nothing about Jordan. Will be a complete disappointment for those who are huge fans or already know a lot about him. <br/><br/>Regardless, the photography is great, albeit small in some places.<br/><br/></span>
